                                                                                              ItsyBitsy — Task-Wise Answers
Task 2 — Burp Suite Basics

• Type of HTTP method used in the first request: → POST
• Parameter that carried the username value: → username
• Parameter that carried the password value: → password

Task 3 — The ItsyBitsy Spider

• Source of the username list for brute force: → rockyou.txt
• Number of total login attempts needed: → 98
• Valid credential found:
→ itsytan:Spider123

Task 4 — Brute Forcing Password

• Tool used to test credentials: → Hydra
• Module/protocol used for brute forcing: → http-post-form

Task 5 — Shell Access

• Command to get a shell as www-data:

sudo -u www-data bash

Task 6 — Privilege Escalation

• File that provided SUID binary: → its_delete
• Final flag path:

/root/its_bitsy_flag.txt


• Contents of the root flag: → THM{its_bitsy_spider_caught}
